  neural net (checkpoints/best.pt) sims=800                bot 12- 0- 0  (100%)  walls=6 (0% useful)  avg_delay/wall=1.00  avg_plies=16

Interpretation:
  - bot win-rate < 50% → losing to a trivial 'walk-around-walls' strategy
  - useful_walls % low → walls placed are easy to walk around (1-square detour)
  - avg_delay/wall ~1.0 → walls are wasted (rusher just sidesteps)
  - avg_delay/wall ≥ 3.0 → walls force real detours (good)
  - if AB high useful% but NN low → NN policy is the bug (aux-value teaches path-counting)
  - if both have low useful% → wall-pruning or eval is the bug
